<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-11-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-11-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="21" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d21">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Furniss</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Port au
                                        Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-11-08"><hi rend="italic">November 8,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 122.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I am in receipt of department’s No. 46 of
                            October 23, 1906, and am pleased to state that the case therein
                            mentioned was settled agreeable to my contentions, as stated in my No.
                            115 of October 30, 1906.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">H. W. Furniss.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>